<item>
            <title>[PIG-4079] Parallel clause is not honored in local mode</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-4079</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I want to debug my custom partitioner in local mode. But it&apos;s not possible with Pig because:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;MR does not invoke partitioner if # of reducers is equal to 1.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAPREDUCE-1287&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAPREDUCE-1287&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Pig always forces a single reducers in local mode.
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;LogicalPlanBuilder.java&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
     void setParallel(LogicalRelationalOperator op, &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Integer&lt;/span&gt; parallel) {
         &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt;( parallel != &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt; ) {
            op.setRequestedParallelism( pigContext.getExecType() == ExecType.LOCAL ? 1 : parallel );
         }
     }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;After I change Pig to honor the parallel clause, my custom partitioner gets invoked in local mode.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
